<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10109066>
    dc:description "FIGURE 26. Genus Prosopogryllacris: A–E, P. p. personata (Serville, 1831) male; F–I, P. p. moeschi (Griffini, 1908) female; J–L, P. labaumei (Griffini, 1912) male (J) and female holotype (K–L); M–N, P. nigrovenosa (Karny, 1928); O, P. nigra sp. nov.—Habitus dorsal view (A, F, J), face (B, G), male abdominal apex in oblique lateral (C), apical (D, M), and ventral view (E, N), female end of abdomen with seventh sternite, subgenital plate and base of ovipositor in ventral (H–I, K) and lateral view (L), stridulatory pegs on second and third abdominal tergites (front is left, O). Scales 10 mm (A, F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10109066/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

